Review: The greatest thing I’ve ever watched at 3AM. I have no idea how I found this.
Unique and fun debut by Jake Johnson. I love the whole cast. Kinda just wish it wrapped things up with in a better way with him and Anna Kendrick’s character. I love Andy Samberg.
A super strong directorial debut. But damn to go from this to Maestro is astounding.
I love how Spike sits in the chair like an elf. Such a mischievous little dude.
I guess I love this Barbie shit.
An incredible directorial debut and a super unique take on the noir. Incredible performances from an insanely unique lead trio.
They didn’t quite find their groove yet. Some stuff falls flat. Still incredible and something to revisit every few years.

Not an easy watch. The cast is great. Incredible filmmaking. I wish it was a little more precise with its perspective so that I had more of a connection to a few more characters. The hard switches from extreme wides to extreme closeups really put us right in the action with the team trying to survive. Great flick!
A goddamn masterpiece.
5 stars good chap!
Awesome visuals but lacking in story.
